(b) "Complaint" means a representation in writing or through other modes alleging
deficiency in service on the part of the PPI issuer with or without seeking relief
thereon;

(d) "Deficiency in service" means a shortcoming or an inadequacy in any service,
which the PPI issuer is required to provide statutorily or otherwise, which may or
may not result in financial loss or damage to the customer;

All complaints
that are partially resolved or wholly rejected by the PPI issuer's internal grievance redress
mechanism shall be auto escalated to the office of the IO for review;
